ZH: 我不相信诅咒的存在。
EN: I don't believe in curses.
ZH: 这本书里讲述了一个被诅咒的古老王国。
EN: This book tells the story of an ancient kingdom cursed.
ZH: 他因诅咒而失去了一切。
EN: He lost everything due to a curse.
ZH: 那个地方据说被诅咒了数百年。
EN: That place is said to have been cursed for hundreds of years.
ZH: 她似乎受到了某种诅咒。
EN: She seems to be under some kind of curse.
ZH: 经过几个月的诅咒，他终于痊愈了。
EN: After months of being cursed, he finally recovered.
ZH: 传说只有一个神能解除诅咒。
EN: Legend has it that only one god can lift the curse.
ZH: 她为了解开诅咒，在世界各地寻找着线索。
EN: She travels around the world searching for clues to break the curse.
ZH: 孩子们被诅咒的姥姥引来了危险。
EN: The children were lured into danger by the cursed grandmother.
ZH: 那把古老的刀剑被诅咒了。
EN: That ancient sword is cursed.
ZH: 这个城市的统治者诅咒了所有的反抗者。
EN: The ruler of this city has cursed all the rebels.
ZH: 有人声称这座建筑物被诅咒了。
EN: Some claim that this building is cursed.
ZH: 我们无法逃过那个诅咒。
EN: We couldn't escape from that curse.
ZH: 那个部落的酋长对我们说了一段长篇诅咒。
EN: The chief of that tribe cast a long curse upon us.
ZH: 昨晚我被一个可怕的诅咒所困扰。
EN: I was haunted by a dreadful curse last night.
ZH: 他们说这座森林被诅咒了。
EN: They say this forest is cursed.
ZH: 这个城市陷入了一场可怕的诅咒。
EN: The city fell under a terrible curse.
ZH: 我们将会对敌人施放一道致命的诅咒。
EN: We will cast a deadly curse on our enemies.
ZH: 她用魔法解开了那个被诅咒的箱子。
EN: She used magic to unlock the cursed box.
ZH: 那个巫师给了我一颗能够解除诅咒的草药。
EN: The wizard gave me an herb that can break the curse.
